gomodel:SYNGO_5585  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: 5-HT4R activation increases cofilin phosphorylation and induces spine maturation in hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 4: 5-HT4R activation boosts the RhoA activity and accumulation of F-actin within individual spines.\n\nFigure 5: 5-HT4R/RhoA signaling mediates dendritic spine maturation in the hippocampal tissue.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal cultures were prepared from C57BL6/J mice and from the B6;129SvEv-Htr4 mice (WT+/+, KO-/-)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-29" ;
